# 🔷 ❗ Your Error

```text
image ".../ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23" not found
```

👉 This does **NOT mean mirror failed**

👉 It means:
❌ You are using **wrong image reference**

---

# 🔷 🔥 Key Concept (VERY IMPORTANT)

OpenShift release images in mirror are:

👉 **digest-based (sha256)**
👉 NOT always tag-based (`:4.19.23`)

---

# 🔷 🔍 What oc-mirror actually created

Your release image is stored like:

```text
bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4@sha256:xxxx
```

NOT:

```text
...:4.19.23  ❌
```

---

# 🔷 ✅ Correct Way to Find Release Image

Go to:

```bash
cd /root/mirror_4_19_23/working-dir
```

Then check:

```bash
cat mapping.txt | grep ocp-release
```

OR:

```bash
cat mapping.txt | grep 4.19.23
```

---

### 🔍 You’ll see something like:

```text
quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-release@sha256:abcd1234 \
→ bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4@sha256:abcd1234
```

---

# 🔷 ✅ Correct command (IMPORTANT)

Use **digest**, not tag:

```bash
oc adm release info \
bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4@sha256:<digest>
```

---

# 🔷 🔥 Why tag doesn’t work?

Because:

* oc-mirror pushes images **by digest**
* It does NOT always create `:4.19.23` tag

---

# 🔷 ✅ Optional (If you WANT tag)

You can tag manually:

```bash
podman pull bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4@sha256:<digest>

podman tag \
bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4@sha256:<digest> \
bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23

podman push bastion.srib-lab-ocp.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23
```

